### 2. Box Sizing Reset, Typography Inheritance, and Default Padding
The component MUST include a box-sizing reset scoped to its root, typography inheritance, and default padding on the root element:
```css
.wf-{{ classPrefix }} *,
.wf-{{ classPrefix }} *::before,
.wf-{{ classPrefix }} *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

.wf-{{ classPrefix }} {
  font-family: inherit;
  color: inherit;
  line-height: inherit;
  padding: 24px;
}
```
The box-sizing reset prevents `width: 100%` elements with padding/border from overflowing their containers.
The default `padding: 24px` on the root element is CRITICAL because in Webflow, code components are often dropped directly onto the page or into a section without a wrapper div. Without padding, content sits flush against the edges. Designers can always override this in Webflow, but the default should look good out of the box.

